<br>
Battle One:<br>
The Dwarfs were trying to land on a strip of beach that held a small garrison of empire scum.  Thank Grungi that the shots from his cannon and morter were off the mark.  All but two of the six boats were able to hit the beach safely.  Once on the beach the might of the dwarven warriors quickly destroyed the Empire, taking only a few deaths  to the Volley Gun on the shore.<br>
<br>
Battle Two:<br>
Out maned 2:1, the dwarves had to break through enemy lines and across a marsh.  It was brutal and bloody.  But in the end The General and Thane were the only ones still breathing and less and four feet tall.  However, my general was responsible for carving the Empire's general and his retinue to shreads.  Earning more than enough points for a vistory.<br>
<br>
Battle Three:<br>
As the Dwarf army was able to move further into the island, we meet a larg Empire army waiting for us near some magical stones.  The human wizzard was powerful inside of the stones, but our runemaster was more than able to keep him in control and some cannons and warriors brought him out of his saddle without too much damage being done.  Once again, the dwarfen general and his bodyguard of hammerers were able to destroy yet another unit of Empire knights and slay thier general.  Thus drawing the surrender of the wretched humans.<br>
<br>
Battle Four:<br>
The stunties chased the remander of the Human force to a defended castle deep within the realm of Albion.  It was a brutal battle- the humans were allowed guns, the attacking dwarfs were not.  On the next to last turn of the game, the Thane was able to open the gates of the castle and then on the last turn the handgunners were able to occupy the gates, earning the victory.<br>
<br>
Battle Five:<br>
The last great battle will take place soon.  We haven't been able to play in about three weeks due to vacations and such, but this one will be fun.  No ranged shooting basically (ALbion weather table).  <br>
We played all of the scenarios in the Albion campaign book.  They are all tons of fun, except the castle storming one (that was just brutal!!!). I still dont know how I won that one.<br>
<br>
I did submitt all of the results to GW! as a good little GW junkie will do.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
